        <h1>About traceability</h1>
        &lt;p&gt;Location: &lt;strong&gt;Asset page &amp;gt; Traceability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In Collibra Data Governance Center, you can display an asset&#39;s traceability. Traceability is essential for impact analysis. This feature helps you to quickly see to which other assets a specific asset is connected. Two assets are connected if you can navigate from one asset to another by traversing one or more relations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;With this feature, you can keep track of:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: square;&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;Relationships between assets, even if they are indirect&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;People involved with a specific asset&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;References in other assets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example: You can check the governance resources to which an asset is connected. You can find in which database tables a certain business term is stored.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Not every relation that is displayed in an asset&#39;s &lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt; tab is taken into account for the traceability.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt; tab displays each relation type that is defined in the attribute assignment group of the asset type and the first relation type in a trace.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Traceability&lt;/strong&gt; tab displays each relation type that is defined in the traceability assignment group of the asset type.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
